cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using machine learning techniques. The use of random forest classifiers and optimal graph segmentation also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the data used in the study is from the osteoarthritis initiative (OAI) database suggests that it could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the use of cost functions and optimization techniques suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
